      "comment": "SWEET AMOUR (6) has been racing well of late. Finished second at her latest appearance over 1680m at this track, beaten 2 metres. Has the ability to take care of this field. QUEENOFDANCE NZ (8) had been racing in great heart then was again in fine form last start when she finished second over 2180m at Burnie, beaten a neck to make it three minor placings from her past four starts. May need luck at some stage extracting from the inside of the second row but meets a similar line up so she can keep the ball rolling. LALIBELA NZ (7) is the next best after finishing third over 2180m at Burnie last time out. Top-three commodity. TALK IS CHEAP (4) is better than her last-start seventh over 1609m at Hobart. Worth another chance.",
